<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>The Network Anomaly Detection System is designed to monitor network traffic for security purposes. All data collected is used solely for detecting potential security threats and is handled in accordance with your organization's data privacy policies.</p>

<h2>Data Collection</h2>
<p>Our system collects the following network traffic information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Source and destination IP addresses</li>
    <li>Port numbers</li>
    <li>Protocol information</li>
    <li>Data transfer volumes</li>
    <li>Connection durations</li>
    <li>User agent strings (when available)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Usage</h2>
<p>The collected data is processed by our machine learning algorithms to identify patterns that may indicate security threats. This information is stored securely and is accessible only to authorized personnel.</p>

<h2>Data Retention</h2>
<p>Network traffic logs are retained for a period of 90 days, after which they are automatically purged from the system unless flagged for further investigation.</p>

